 "date": "1984-06-12", "label": "Frank Sinatra, Singer", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["drums"], "works": [{"t": "Selections (unspecified)", "c": null, "w": "104450"}]}, {"id": "41978", "date": "1984-06-15", "label": "Frank Sinatra, Singer", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["drums"], "works": [{"t": "Selections (unspecified)", "c": null, "w": "104450"}]}, {"id": "41979", "date": "1984-06-16", "label": "Frank Sinatra, Singer", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["drums"], "works": [{"t": "Selections (unspecified)", "c": null, "w": "104450"}]}, {"id": "41980", "date": "1984-06-17", "label": "Frank Sinatra, Singer", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["drums"], "works": [{"t": "Selections (unspecified)", "c": null, "w": "104450"}]}], "works_created": [], "quotes": [], "about_quotes": [{"speaker": "Ignacio Berroa", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "[INTERVIEWER] When I was in college a certain group of us, we would have dreams about getting a call to play with Buddy Rich or Stan Kenton. You know I dreamt about being a member of Blood, Sweat & Tears. [INTERVIEWEE] Wow.", "doc_title": "Ignacio Berroa interviewed by Monk Rowe, via Zoom, October 22, 2021 [interview 2 of 2]", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/ignacio-berroa-interviewed-monk-rowe-zoom-october-22-2021-interview-2-2"}, {"speaker": "Sherrie Maricle", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "I saw all of those bands... I saw Buddy Rich and his Killer Force Orchestra, and that was when I was eleven that I said that was exactly what I wanted to do then was just play the drums.", "doc_title": "Sherrie Maricle interviewed by Monk Rowe, Clearwater Beach, Florida, March 18, 2001 [interview 1 of 2]", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/sherrie-maricle-interviewed-monk-rowe-clearwater-beach-florida-march-18-2001"}, {"speaker": "John Altman", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "And he actually introduced Artie Shaw to Buddy Rich, whom he heard playing in a club with I think it might have been Bobby Hackett or Adrian Rollini or someone like that.", "doc_title": "John Altman interviewed by Monk Rowe, via Zoom, September 14, 2023", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/john-altman-interviewed-monk-rowe-zoom-september-14-2023"}, {"speaker": "Harry Edison", "relation": "collaborated with", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "Yeah, Buddy Rich, 1951, he got a band together, he had a five piece band, with Zoot Sims and myself... I played with Buddy quite a bit. We became very close friends.", "doc_title": "Harry Edison — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://amhistory.si.edu/jazz/Edison-Harry/Edison_Harry_Interview_Transcription.pdf"}, {"speaker": "Ernie Watts", "relation": "played under", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "So I was the kid that got recommended, and I joined Buddy Rich’s band and I was there for two years. And I made three or four records with Buddy.", "doc_title": "Ernie Watts interviewed by Monk Rowe, Toronto, Canada, January 11, 2003", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/ernie-watts-interviewed-monk-rowe-toronto-canada-january-11-2003"}, {"speaker": "Tom Malone", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "[INTERVIEWER] ...we all had aspirations to maybe get in a big band, oh my God if we could get in Buddy Rich’s big band.", "doc_title": "Tom Malone interviewed by Monk Rowe, via Zoom, May 3, 2023", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/tom-malone-interviewed-monk-rowe-zoom-may-3-2023"}]}